pr_review_body:
Thanks very much for this! I left two suggestions for your consideration.

@StrikerRUS since we haven't been successful getting any other reviews with more OpenCL understanding to review...could you test the generated wheels one more time? There have been some additional commits since you last tested (https://github.com/microsoft/LightGBM/pull/5252#issuecomment-1159807098).

I'm also interested in understanding how much larger the package's wheels will be as a result of this change. Large wheels can introduce some new classes of problems for users (for example, those using function-as-a-service services that have fairly strict limits on disk usage, see https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/issues/30741#issuecomment-752751976). I'll wait until another commit is pushed to check that (since the previous Azure DevOps build is gone now).

