@codewithnick Well done 🔥 
I comment on some minor issues.
Please address them, after that we will merge this PR 🚀

I really like what I'm seeing here. Though I think it's about time to split up fluidsynth.py, since we already at this point have massive trouble merging code back.

I think every class should have its own file, that would make code changes a heck of a lot easier.

@SpotlightKid Thanks for the effort you put in this. I'm sorry I didn't respond earlier

I'm uncertain if I understand the implementation method of the PR, why does the `click` example you posted in the PR description reimplement the `conda` main command?

Do you think non-grouped click commands work with this? Do we need to pass to click (or other CLI libraries like typer) additional information what has alredy been parsed by the main argparse parser (e.g. `sys.argv[1:]`)?

From the click example, does this work?
```
import click

from conda.plugins import hookimpl, CondaSubcommand


@click.command()
@click.option('--count', default=1, help='Number of greetings.')
@click.option('--name', prompt='Your name',
              help='The person to greet.')
def hello(count, name):
    """Simple program that greets NAME for a total of COUNT times."""
    for x in range(count):
        click.echo(f"Hello {name}!")


@hookimpl
def conda_subcommands():
    yield CondaSubcommand(
        name="my_command",
        summary=hello.__doc__,
        action=hello,
        pass_sys_argv=False,
    )
```

I think it would be simpler to handle this in a more general case. After we set `typ = codegen.UnwrapType(type)`, we could put 
```go
if union, ok := typ.(*schema.UnionType); ok {
  typ = reduceUnion(union, value)
}
```

Reduce union would look like
```
// reduceUnion returns the element type in union that bests fits value.
// If more than one type fits, reduceUnion will return the first type in union.Elements.
// If no type fits, union.DefaultType is returned. The default type may be `nil`.
func reduceUnion(union *schema.UnionType, value resource.PropertyValue) schema.Type
```

`UnionType.Discriminator` is optional, so we will need to reduce based on the shape of the value, not just on the discriminator.
